WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Good morning, Jacob. Friday, April twenty-fourth. Project Arete day twelve

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
of thirty. Today's lead is unusual. Yesterday's briefing was wrong

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:12.000
about the most important story of your day, and we

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
owe you a retraction before we owe you anything else.

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
The memory file said you sent a ten-fifteen PM direct

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.000
message to Katelyn about not feeling responded-to on the intimate

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
thread of the relationship, and that it sat unread. Neither

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
thing happened. What did happen: you and Katelyn had an

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
hour-long conversation between eight-fifty-two and nine-forty-seven PM about the future.

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
Moving. A plan. The fact that you don't have one.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.000
It ended mutually, with her saying, quote, I mean yeah

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
but we can talk later. And then she came back

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
warm. Merlin bird photos at ten-thirty-one. Post-midnight-movie texts at one-twenty

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:56.000
AM about a film she cried at in a good

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:00.000
way, and a Reddit rabbit hole on Whoop and Lumia

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.000
earrings. The thread isn't stalled. It tapped out at bedtime.

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:08.000
Your job today is to put a real time on

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:12.000
later before later drifts into next week and your flights

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:16.000
are the thing that almost happened. On Anthropic: quieter Friday.

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.000
The NEC partnership dropped yesterday evening Japan time — Japan's

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.000
largest AI engineering workforce, thin on specifics. Boris Cherny published

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
the Claude Code post-mortem. Three technical changes compounded into what

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:32.000
users were calling the model getting dumber, limits reset for

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:36.000
everyone on April twentieth. Community is mixed but softer than

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:40.000
Wednesday. Anthropic-over-OpenAI 2026 drifted down four points on Manifold despite

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:44.000
the trillion-dollar secondary story. DeepSeek shipped V4 overnight. Two preview

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:48.000
models. The Pro tier is the largest open weights model

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:52.000
ever released. The Flash tier is the cheapest small model,

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:56.000
full stop. Simon Willison's write-up landed at six-oh-one this morning.

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.000
Twenty minutes today is worth it. Iran: Trump ordered shoot-and-kill

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.000
on IRGC mine-laying boats. Ceasefire framing survives; rules of engagement

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:08.000
didn't. Dustin is five days stale. Alex Kelley has three

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:12.000
items stacked. One paragraph closes the thread. Have a good

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:12.400
day.
